[There, unfortunately, have been 31 cases of mumps in Hawaii with complications, including loss of hearing. With the exception of children who have underlying conditions that prevent them from being vaccinated, all other children old enough to be vaccinated should be, not only to protect themselves, but also to protect others who cannot be safely vaccinated. With 1000 cases, there must be a low proportion of children vaccinated, especially on Oahu. - Mod.LK

